      "content": "i hear u, but some people argue that unions actually hurt the economy by driving up costs and making it harder for companies to hire new people or adapt to change. if a company has to pay way more just because of a union, doesn't that risk them moving jobs overseas or just going out of business? seems like a huge trade off.",
